{"title": "Should Singapore contribute to COP27 loss and damage fund?", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2022-12-09", "content": "A key outcome of the recently concluded COP27 United Nations climate change summit in Egypt was the agreement to set up a loss and damage fund. The global fund, hailed as a breakthrough deal, will provide financial aid to poorer countries hit by climate disasters.\nSingapore\u2019s Minister for Sustainability and the Environment Grace Fu welcomed it as a positive move, but said that the possibility of the Republic contributing to a donor base for climate finance was still to be negotiated."}